":0},"body":"**Describe the bug**\r\nCatch2 marks tests as failed when a continuable C0000005 exception is raised and caught by a test. \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nTests should be marked as failed only when non-continuable exceptions are raised or exceptions are not handled.\r\n\r\n**Reproduction steps**\r\nSteps to reproduce the bug.\r\n```\r\n#define CATCH_CONFIG_MAIN\r\n\r\n#include <iostream>\r\n#include <Windows.h>\r\n#include \"catch2\\catch.hpp\"\r\n\r\nvoid throw_and_catch()\r\n{\r\n    __try {\r\n        RaiseException(0xC0000005, 0, 0, NULL);\r\n    }\r\n    __except (1)\r\n    {\r\n\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\nTEST_CASE(\"foo\", \"[bar]\")\r\n{\r\n    throw_and_catch();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Platform information:**\r\n<!-- Fill in any extra information that might be important for your issue. -->\r\n - OS: Windows 11, build 22523.1002.amd64fre.rs_onecore_stack.211210-1950\r\n - Compiler+version: VS 2022 / CL version 19.30.30706.\r\n - Catch version: 2.8.0\r\n\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nThe Visual Studio AddressSanitizer relies on catching and handling 0xC0000005 structured exceptions as part of its logic. This behavior in Catch breaks ASAN.\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/events{/privacy}","received_eve